basics.label: Biomedical Engineering Technician II
basics.summary: Versatile BMET II highly effective at working independently and as part of a team. Expertise in installation and inspection of medical devices.

work.name: Company Name
work.summary: Properly respond to service calls to evaluate, diagnose, perform repair and planned maintenance on hospital's biomedical equipment. Knowledge of application and repair of computers and servers and how they interface medical equipment. Ensure all work orders, vendor service reports, PM activities, purchase orders and other duties are documented in an accurate and timely manner.
highlights: Promoted to one of 3 Lead Techs overseeing Preventive Maintenance (PM) inspections
Evaluate biomedical equipment issues, implement appropriate repairs
Assist other technicians on basic and complex repairs
Integration of software for network systems such as Philips, Hillrom, and Hugs Infant Security System
